{
  "video_id": "V1ItvwxBENg",
  "title": "Economic growth has stalled. Let's fix it | Dambisa Moyo",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13359.0,
      "end_time": 18456.0,
      "text": "Our ability to create and sustain economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 18480.0,
      "end_time": 21216.0,
      "text": "is the defining challenge of our time."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21240.0,
      "end_time": 23776.0,
      "text": "Of course there are other challenges --"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23800.0,
      "end_time": 26936.0,
      "text": "health care, disease burdens and pandemics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26960.0,
      "end_time": 28760.0,
      "text": "environmental challenges"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29400.0,
      "end_time": 32800.0,
      "text": "and, of course, radicalized terrorism."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 32800.0,
      "end_time": 34160.0,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34400.0,
      "end_time": 38616.0,
      "text": "to the extent that we can actually solve the economic growth challenge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38640.0,
      "end_time": 39976.0,
      "text": "it will take us a long way"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40000.0,
      "end_time": 42600.0,
      "text": "to solving the challenges that I&#39;ve just elucidated."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43400.0,
      "end_time": 45560.0,
      "text": "More importantly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 45800.0,
      "end_time": 49576.0,
      "text": "unless and until we solve economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 49600.0,
      "end_time": 53616.0,
      "text": "and create sustainable, long-term economic growth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53640.0,
      "end_time": 56560.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ll be unable to address"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 56800.0,
      "end_time": 61416.0,
      "text": "the seemingly intractable challenges that continue to pervade the globe today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61440.0,
      "end_time": 65840.0,
      "text": "whether it&#39;s health care, education or economic development."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 66680.0,
      "end_time": 68880.0,
      "text": "The fundamental question is this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 69520.0,
      "end_time": 72136.0,
      "text": "How are we going to create economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 72160.0,
      "end_time": 76735.0,
      "text": "in advanced and developed economies like the United States and across Europe"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 76760.0,
      "end_time": 78816.0,
      "text": "at a time when they continue to struggle"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 78840.0,
      "end_time": 81640.0,
      "text": "to create economic growth after the financial crisis?"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 82480.0,
      "end_time": 85256.0,
      "text": "They continue to underperform"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 85280.0,
      "end_time": 89400.0,
      "text": "and to see an erosion in the three key drivers of economic growth:"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 90400.0,
      "end_time": 93360.0,
      "text": "capital, labor and productivity."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 94120.0,
      "end_time": 95576.0,
      "text": "In particular,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 95600.0,
      "end_time": 100536.0,
      "text": "these developed economies continue to see debts and deficits,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 100560.0,
      "end_time": 105416.0,
      "text": "the decline and erosion of both the quality and quantity of labor"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 105440.0,
      "end_time": 107720.0,
      "text": "and they also see productivity stalling."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 108600.0,
      "end_time": 110295.0,
      "text": "In a similar vein,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 110320.0,
      "end_time": 113735.0,
      "text": "how are we going to create economic growth in the emerging markets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 113760.0,
      "end_time": 117160.0,
      "text": "where 90 percent of the world&#39;s population lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 117400.0,
      "end_time": 118576.0,
      "text": "and where, on average,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 118600.0,
      "end_time": 122119.0,
      "text": "70 percent of the population is under the age of 25?"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 122640.0,
      "end_time": 124960.0,
      "text": "In these countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 124120.0,
      "end_time": 128295.0,
      "text": "it is essential that they grow at a minimum of seven percent a year"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 128320.0,
      "end_time": 130416.0,
      "text": "in order to put a dent in poverty"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 130440.0,
      "end_time": 133640.0,
      "text": "and to double per capita incomes in one generation."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 134520.0,
      "end_time": 136576.0,
      "text": "And yet today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 136600.0,
      "end_time": 138696.0,
      "text": "the largest emerging economies --"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 138720.0,
      "end_time": 141416.0,
      "text": "countries with at least 50 million people --"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 141440.0,
      "end_time": 144920.0,
      "text": "continue to struggle to reach that seven percent magic mark."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 145760.0,
      "end_time": 146976.0,
      "text": "Worse than that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 147000.0,
      "end_time": 151616.0,
      "text": "countries like India, Russia, South Africa, Brazil and even China"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 151640.0,
      "end_time": 154136.0,
      "text": "are falling below that seven percent number"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 154160.0,
      "end_time": 157000.0,
      "text": "and, in many cases, actually regressing."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 157800.0,
      "end_time": 159720.0,
      "text": "Economic growth matters."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 160440.0,
      "end_time": 161896.0,
      "text": "With economic growth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 161920.0,
      "end_time": 166950.0,
      "text": "countries and societies enter into a virtuous cycle"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 166120.0,
      "end_time": 170720.0,
      "text": "of upward mobility, opportunity and improved living standards."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 171240.0,
      "end_time": 175560.0,
      "text": "Without growth, countries contract and atrophy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 175800.0,
      "end_time": 178296.0,
      "text": "not just in the annals of economic statistics"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 178320.0,
      "end_time": 181840.0,
      "text": "but also in the meaning of life and how lives are lived."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 182600.0,
      "end_time": 186320.0,
      "text": "Economic growth matters powerfully for the individual."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 187120.0,
      "end_time": 188736.0,
      "text": "If growth wanes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 188760.0,
      "end_time": 190775.0,
      "text": "the risk to human progress"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 190800.0,
      "end_time": 195216.0,
      "text": "and the risk of political and social instability rises,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 195240.0,
      "end_time": 199800.0,
      "text": "and societies become dimmer, coarser and smaller."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 200600.0,
      "end_time": 202296.0,
      "text": "The context matters."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 202320.0,
      "end_time": 203936.0,
      "text": "And countries in emerging markets"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 203960.0,
      "end_time": 207800.0,
      "text": "do not need to grow at the same rates as developed countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 209240.0,
      "end_time": 213680.0,
      "text": "Now, I know some of you in this room find this to be a risky proposition."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 214680.0,
      "end_time": 216536.0,
      "text": "There are some people here"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 216560.0,
      "end_time": 219960.0,
      "text": "who will turn around and be quite disillusioned"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 219120.0,
      "end_time": 220896.0,
      "text": "by what&#39;s happened around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 220920.0,
      "end_time": 223519.0,
      "text": "and basically ascribe that to economic growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 224240.0,
      "end_time": 227736.0,
      "text": "You worry about the overpopulation of the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 227760.0,
      "end_time": 230655.0,
      "text": "And looking at the UN&#39;s recent statistics and projections"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 230680.0,
      "end_time": 233376.0,
      "text": "that the world will have 11 billion people on the planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 233400.0,
      "end_time": 235976.0,
      "text": "before it plateaus in 2100,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 236000.0,
      "end_time": 239816.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re concerned about what that does to natural resources --"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 239840.0,
      "end_time": 243960.0,
      "text": "arable land, potable water, energy and minerals."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 244800.0,
      "end_time": 248120.0,
      "text": "You are also concerned about the degradation of the environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 248760.0,
      "end_time": 251896.0,
      "text": "And you worry about how man,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 251920.0,
      "end_time": 254536.0,
      "text": "embodied in the corporate globalist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 254560.0,
      "end_time": 257600.0,
      "text": "has become greedy and corrupt."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 258560.0,
      "end_time": 261935.0,
      "text": "But I&#39;m here to tell you today that economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 261959.0,
      "end_time": 265335.0,
      "text": "has been the backbone of changes in living standards"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 265360.0,
      "end_time": 267320.0,
      "text": "of millions of people around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 267960.0,
      "end_time": 269775.0,
      "text": "And more importantly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 269800.0,
      "end_time": 274280.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s not just economic growth that has been driven by capitalism."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 276280.0,
      "end_time": 279736.0,
      "text": "The definition of capitalism, very simply put,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 279760.0,
      "end_time": 281816.0,
      "text": "is that the factors of production,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 281840.0,
      "end_time": 285215.0,
      "text": "such as trade and industry, capital and labor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 285240.0,
      "end_time": 289160.0,
      "text": "are left in the hands of the private sector and not the state."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 289680.0,
      "end_time": 292416.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really essential here that we understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 292440.0,
      "end_time": 297456.0,
      "text": "that fundamentally the critique is not for economic growth per se"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 297480.0,
      "end_time": 299536.0,
      "text": "but what has happened to capitalism."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 299560.0,
      "end_time": 303576.0,
      "text": "And to the extent that we need to create economic growth over the long term,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 303600.0,
      "end_time": 308280.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to have to pursue it with a better form of economic stance."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 309320.0,
      "end_time": 312216.0,
      "text": "Economic growth needs capitalism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 312240.0,
      "end_time": 313920.0,
      "text": "but it needs it to work properly."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 314840.0,
      "end_time": 317135.0,
      "text": "And as I mentioned a moment ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 317160.0,
      "end_time": 323120.0,
      "text": "the core of the capitalist system has been defined by private actors."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 323720.0,
      "end_time": 327776.0,
      "text": "And even this, however, is a very simplistic dichotomy."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 327800.0,
      "end_time": 330720.0,
      "text": "Capitalism: good; non-capitalism: bad."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 331120.0,
      "end_time": 333776.0,
      "text": "When in practical experience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 333800.0,
      "end_time": 336256.0,
      "text": "capitalism is much more of a spectrum."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 336280.0,
      "end_time": 338535.0,
      "text": "And we have countries such as China,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 338560.0,
      "end_time": 340976.0,
      "text": "which have practiced more state capitalism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 341000.0,
      "end_time": 343960.0,
      "text": "and we have countries like the Unites States"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 343120.0,
      "end_time": 344720.0,
      "text": "which are more market capitalist."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 345160.0,
      "end_time": 348296.0,
      "text": "Our efforts to critique the capitalist system, however,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 348320.0,
      "end_time": 351536.0,
      "text": "have tended to focus on countries like China"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 351560.0,
      "end_time": 354960.0,
      "text": "that are in fact not blatantly market capitalism."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 355600.0,
      "end_time": 359256.0,
      "text": "However, there is a real reason and real concern"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 359280.0,
      "end_time": 363936.0,
      "text": "for us to now focus our attentions on purer forms of capitalism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 363960.0,
      "end_time": 366680.0,
      "text": "particularly those embodied by the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 367280.0,
      "end_time": 369560.0,
      "text": "This is really important"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 369800.0,
      "end_time": 371536.0,
      "text": "because this type of capitalism"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 371560.0,
      "end_time": 374816.0,
      "text": "has increasingly been afforded the critique"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 374840.0,
      "end_time": 377256.0,
      "text": "that it is now fostering corruption"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 377280.0,
      "end_time": 378655.0,
      "text": "and, worse still,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 378680.0,
      "end_time": 381320.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s increasing income inequality --"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 382120.0,
      "end_time": 386840.0,
      "text": "the idea that the few are benefiting at the expense of the many."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 388760.0,
      "end_time": 391976.0,
      "text": "The two really critical questions that we need to address"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 392000.0,
      "end_time": 394696.0,
      "text": "is how can we fix capitalism"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 394720.0,
      "end_time": 397496.0,
      "text": "so that it can help create economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 397520.0,
      "end_time": 400880.0,
      "text": "but at the same time can help to address social ills."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 401720.0,
      "end_time": 405960.0,
      "text": "In order to think about that framing, we have to ask ourselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 405120.0,
      "end_time": 406840.0,
      "text": "how does capitalism work today?"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 407760.0,
      "end_time": 409360.0,
      "text": "Very simplistically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 409960.0,
      "end_time": 415736.0,
      "text": "capitalism is set on the basis of an individual utility maximizer --"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 415760.0,
      "end_time": 420560.0,
      "text": "a selfish individual who goes after what he or she wants."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 420800.0,
      "end_time": 423216.0,
      "text": "And only after they&#39;ve maximized their utility"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 423240.0,
      "end_time": 425736.0,
      "text": "do they then decide it&#39;s important"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 425760.0,
      "end_time": 428840.0,
      "text": "to provide support to other social contracts."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 429360.0,
      "end_time": 432776.0,
      "text": "Of course, in this system governments do tax,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 432800.0,
      "end_time": 436536.0,
      "text": "and they use part of their revenues to fund social programs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 436560.0,
      "end_time": 439416.0,
      "text": "recognizing that government&#39;s role is not just regulation"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 439440.0,
      "end_time": 442719.0,
      "text": "but also to be arbiter of social goods."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 443320.0,
      "end_time": 444616.0,
      "text": "But nevertheless,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 444640.0,
      "end_time": 445976.0,
      "text": "this framework --"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 446000.0,
      "end_time": 447976.0,
      "text": "this two-stage framework --"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 448000.0,
      "end_time": 449976.0,
      "text": "is the basis from which we must now start"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 450000.0,
      "end_time": 452600.0,
      "text": "to think about how we can improve the capitalist model."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 453520.0,
      "end_time": 456919.0,
      "text": "I would argue that there are two sides to this challenge."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 457520.0,
      "end_time": 458736.0,
      "text": "First of all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 458760.0,
      "end_time": 461695.0,
      "text": "we can draw on the right-wing policies"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 461720.0,
      "end_time": 463576.0,
      "text": "to see what could be beneficial for us"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 463600.0,
      "end_time": 465720.0,
      "text": "to think about how we can improve capitalism."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 466440.0,
      "end_time": 467695.0,
      "text": "In particular,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 467720.0,
      "end_time": 469456.0,
      "text": "right-leaning policies"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 469480.0,
      "end_time": 472936.0,
      "text": "have tended to focus on things like conditional transfers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 472960.0,
      "end_time": 475976.0,
      "text": "where we pay and reward people for doing the things"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 476000.0,
      "end_time": 479456.0,
      "text": "that we actually think can help enhance economic growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 479480.0,
      "end_time": 480696.0,
      "text": "For example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 480720.0,
      "end_time": 482336.0,
      "text": "sending children to school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 482360.0,
      "end_time": 484576.0,
      "text": "parents could earn money for that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 484600.0,
      "end_time": 487976.0,
      "text": "or getting their children inoculated or immunized,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 488000.0,
      "end_time": 489880.0,
      "text": "parents could get paid for doing that."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 490360.0,
      "end_time": 492456.0,
      "text": "Now, quite apart from the debate"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 492480.0,
      "end_time": 494776.0,
      "text": "on whether or not we should be paying people"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 494800.0,
      "end_time": 497496.0,
      "text": "to do what we think they should do anyway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 497520.0,
      "end_time": 500695.0,
      "text": "the fact of the matter is that pay for performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 500720.0,
      "end_time": 503136.0,
      "text": "has actually yielded some positive results"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 503160.0,
      "end_time": 504856.0,
      "text": "in places like Mexico,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 504880.0,
      "end_time": 506135.0,
      "text": "in Brazil"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 506160.0,
      "end_time": 508760.0,
      "text": "and also in pilot programs in New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 509520.0,
      "end_time": 511150.0,
      "text": "But there are also benefits"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 511400.0,
      "end_time": 515400.0,
      "text": "and significant changes underway on left-leaning policies."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 515880.0,
      "end_time": 520135.0,
      "text": "Arguments that government should expand its role and responsibility"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 520159.0,
      "end_time": 522376.0,
      "text": "so that it&#39;s not so narrowly defined"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 522400.0,
      "end_time": 524895.0,
      "text": "and that government should be much more of an arbiter"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 524919.0,
      "end_time": 526295.0,
      "text": "of the factors of production"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 526320.0,
      "end_time": 528720.0,
      "text": "have become commonplace with the success of China."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 529400.0,
      "end_time": 531696.0,
      "text": "But also we&#39;ve started to have debates"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 531720.0,
      "end_time": 533976.0,
      "text": "about how the role of the private sector"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 534000.0,
      "end_time": 536576.0,
      "text": "should move away from just being a profit motive"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 536600.0,
      "end_time": 540960.0,
      "text": "and really be more engaged in the delivery of social programs."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 540120.0,
      "end_time": 543336.0,
      "text": "Things like the corporate social responsibility programs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 543360.0,
      "end_time": 545336.0,
      "text": "albeit small in scale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 545360.0,
      "end_time": 547240.0,
      "text": "are moving in that right direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 547960.0,
      "end_time": 553176.0,
      "text": "Of course, left-leaning policies have also tended to blur the lines"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 553200.0,
      "end_time": 555880.0,
      "text": "between government, NGOs and private sector."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 556800.0,
      "end_time": 560776.0,
      "text": "Two very good examples of this are the 19th-century United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 560800.0,
      "end_time": 562415.0,
      "text": "when the infrastructure rollout"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 562440.0,
      "end_time": 565536.0,
      "text": "was really about public-private partnerships."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 565560.0,
      "end_time": 566976.0,
      "text": "More recently, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 567000.0,
      "end_time": 570616.0,
      "text": "the advent of the Internet has also proven to the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 570640.0,
      "end_time": 574480.0,
      "text": "that public and private can work together for the betterment of society."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 576240.0,
      "end_time": 579296.0,
      "text": "My fundamental message to you is this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 579320.0,
      "end_time": 584736.0,
      "text": "We cannot continue to try and solve the world economic growth challenges"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 584760.0,
      "end_time": 588920.0,
      "text": "by being dogmatic and being unnecessarily ideological."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 589800.0,
      "end_time": 593616.0,
      "text": "In order to create sustainable, long-term economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 593640.0,
      "end_time": 597936.0,
      "text": "and solve the challenges and social ills that continue to plague the world today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 597960.0,
      "end_time": 600256.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to have to be more broad-minded"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 600280.0,
      "end_time": 601800.0,
      "text": "about what might work."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 602280.0,
      "end_time": 603856.0,
      "text": "Ultimately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 603880.0,
      "end_time": 608160.0,
      "text": "we have to recognize that ideology is the enemy of growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 608400.0,
      "end_time": 609256.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 609280.0,
      "end_time": 611520.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 615160.0,
      "end_time": 618550.0,
      "text": "Bruno Giussani: I want to ask a couple of questions, Dambisa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 618800.0,
      "end_time": 620216.0,
      "text": "because one could react to your last sentence"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 620240.0,
      "end_time": 622560.0,
      "text": "by saying growth is also an ideology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 622800.0,
      "end_time": 624416.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s possibly the dominant ideology of our times."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 624440.0,
      "end_time": 626536.0,
      "text": "What do you say to those who react that way?"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 626560.0,
      "end_time": 629160.0,
      "text": "DM: Well, I think that that&#39;s completely legitimate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 629400.0,
      "end_time": 631616.0,
      "text": "and I think that we&#39;re already having that discussion."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 631640.0,
      "end_time": 633856.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a lot of work going on around happiness"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 633880.0,
      "end_time": 637376.0,
      "text": "and other metrics being used for measuring people&#39;s success"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 637400.0,
      "end_time": 639216.0,
      "text": "and improvements in living standards."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 639240.0,
      "end_time": 641296.0,
      "text": "And so I think that we should be open"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 641320.0,
      "end_time": 644296.0,
      "text": "to what could deliver improvements in people&#39;s living standards"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 644320.0,
      "end_time": 646576.0,
      "text": "and continue to reduce poverty around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 646600.0,
      "end_time": 649416.0,
      "text": "BG: So you&#39;re basically pleading for rehabilitating growth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 649440.0,
      "end_time": 651160.0,
      "text": "but the only way for that happen"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 651400.0,
      "end_time": 653376.0,
      "text": "without compromising the capacity of the earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 653400.0,
      "end_time": 654935.0,
      "text": "to take us on a long journey,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 654960.0,
      "end_time": 656616.0,
      "text": "is for economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 656640.0,
      "end_time": 659336.0,
      "text": "somehow to decouple from the underlying use of resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 659360.0,
      "end_time": 660656.0,
      "text": "Do you see that happening?"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 660680.0,
      "end_time": 665215.0,
      "text": "DM: Well, I think that I&#39;m more optimistic about human ability and ingenuity."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 665240.0,
      "end_time": 667416.0,
      "text": "I think if we start to constrain ourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 667440.0,
      "end_time": 670496.0,
      "text": "using the finite, scarce and depleting resources"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 670520.0,
      "end_time": 671776.0,
      "text": "that we know today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 671800.0,
      "end_time": 673136.0,
      "text": "we could get quite negative"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 673160.0,
      "end_time": 675376.0,
      "text": "and quite concerned about the way the world is."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 675400.0,
      "end_time": 677696.0,
      "text": "However, we&#39;ve seen the Club of Rome,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 677720.0,
      "end_time": 680136.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve seen previous claims"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 680160.0,
      "end_time": 682496.0,
      "text": "that the world would be running out of resources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 682520.0,
      "end_time": 685960.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s not to argue that those things are not valid."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 685120.0,
      "end_time": 687776.0,
      "text": "But I think, with ingenuity we could see desalination,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 687800.0,
      "end_time": 689736.0,
      "text": "I think we could reinvest in energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 689760.0,
      "end_time": 691896.0,
      "text": "so that we can actually get better outcomes."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 691920.0,
      "end_time": 693136.0,
      "text": "And so in that sense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 693160.0,
      "end_time": 695536.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m much more optimistic about what humans can do."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 695560.0,
      "end_time": 696976.0,
      "text": "BG: The thing that strikes me"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 697000.0,
      "end_time": 700376.0,
      "text": "about your proposals for rehabilitating growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 700400.0,
      "end_time": 702160.0,
      "text": "and taking a different direction"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 702400.0,
      "end_time": 707960.0,
      "text": "is that you&#39;re kind of suggesting to fix capitalism with more capitalism --"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 707120.0,
      "end_time": 710736.0,
      "text": "with putting a price tag on good behavior as incentive"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 710760.0,
      "end_time": 714936.0,
      "text": "or developing a bigger role for business in social issues."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 714960.0,
      "end_time": 716456.0,
      "text": "Is that what you&#39;re suggesting?"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 716480.0,
      "end_time": 718616.0,
      "text": "DM: I&#39;m suggesting we have to be open-minded."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 718640.0,
      "end_time": 720856.0,
      "text": "I think it is absolutely the case"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 720880.0,
      "end_time": 723336.0,
      "text": "that traditional models of economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 723360.0,
      "end_time": 725776.0,
      "text": "are not working the way we would like them to."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 725800.0,
      "end_time": 727695.0,
      "text": "And I think it&#39;s no accident"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 727720.0,
      "end_time": 731160.0,
      "text": "that today the largest economy in the world, the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 731400.0,
      "end_time": 732336.0,
      "text": "has democracy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 732360.0,
      "end_time": 735456.0,
      "text": "liberal democracy, as it&#39;s core political stance"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 735480.0,
      "end_time": 737656.0,
      "text": "and it has free market capitalism --"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 737680.0,
      "end_time": 739256.0,
      "text": "to the extent that it is free --"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 739280.0,
      "end_time": 741456.0,
      "text": "free market capitalism as its economic stance."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 741480.0,
      "end_time": 743616.0,
      "text": "The second largest economy is China."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 743640.0,
      "end_time": 745776.0,
      "text": "It has deprioritized democracy"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 745800.0,
      "end_time": 748976.0,
      "text": "and it has state capitalism, which is a completely different model."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 749000.0,
      "end_time": 751736.0,
      "text": "These two countries, completely different political models"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 751760.0,
      "end_time": 753736.0,
      "text": "and completely different economic models,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 753760.0,
      "end_time": 756176.0,
      "text": "and yet they have the same income inequality number"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 756200.0,
      "end_time": 757696.0,
      "text": "measured as a Gini coefficient."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 757720.0,
      "end_time": 759856.0,
      "text": "I think those are the debates we should have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 759880.0,
      "end_time": 762160.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s not clear at all"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 762400.0,
      "end_time": 763856.0,
      "text": "what model we should be adopting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 763880.0,
      "end_time": 766216.0,
      "text": "and I think there needs to be much more discourse"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 766240.0,
      "end_time": 769656.0,
      "text": "and much more humility about what we know and what we don&#39;t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 769680.0,
      "end_time": 773550.0,
      "text": "BG: One last question. The COP21 is going on in Paris."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 773800.0,
      "end_time": 774576.0,
      "text": "If you could send a tweet"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 774600.0,
      "end_time": 777896.0,
      "text": "to all the heads of state and heads of delegations there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 777920.0,
      "end_time": 779295.0,
      "text": "what would you say?"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 779320.0,
      "end_time": 781976.0,
      "text": "DM: Again, I would be very much about being open-minded."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 782000.0,
      "end_time": 783216.0,
      "text": "As you&#39;re aware,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 783240.0,
      "end_time": 785336.0,
      "text": "the issues around the environmental concerns"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 785360.0,
      "end_time": 787336.0,
      "text": "have been on the agenda many times now --"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 787360.0,
      "end_time": 789616.0,
      "text": "in Copenhagen, &#39;72 in Stockholm --"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 789640.0,
      "end_time": 791936.0,
      "text": "and we keep revisiting these issues"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 791960.0,
      "end_time": 795536.0,
      "text": "partly because there is not a fundamental agreement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 795560.0,
      "end_time": 796815.0,
      "text": "in fact there&#39;s a schism"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 796840.0,
      "end_time": 799576.0,
      "text": "between what the developed countries believe and want"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 799600.0,
      "end_time": 801936.0,
      "text": "and what emerging market countries want."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 801960.0,
      "end_time": 805176.0,
      "text": "Emerging market countries need to continue to create economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 805200.0,
      "end_time": 808616.0,
      "text": "so that we don&#39;t have political uncertainty in the those countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 808640.0,
      "end_time": 810776.0,
      "text": "Developed countries recognize"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 810800.0,
      "end_time": 813550.0,
      "text": "that they have a real, important responsibility"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 813800.0,
      "end_time": 815896.0,
      "text": "not only just to manage their CO2 emissions"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 815920.0,
      "end_time": 819960.0,
      "text": "and some of the degradation that they&#39;re contributing to the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 819120.0,
      "end_time": 820896.0,
      "text": "but also as trendsetters in R&D."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 820920.0,
      "end_time": 823175.0,
      "text": "And so they have to come to the table as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 823200.0,
      "end_time": 825656.0,
      "text": "But in essence, it cannot be a situation"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 825680.0,
      "end_time": 829815.0,
      "text": "where we start ascribing policies to the emerging markets"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 829840.0,
      "end_time": 831696.0,
      "text": "without developed countries themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 831720.0,
      "end_time": 834960.0,
      "text": "also taking quite a swipe at what they&#39;re doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 834120.0,
      "end_time": 836896.0,
      "text": "both in demand and supply in developed markets."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 836920.0,
      "end_time": 840160.0,
      "text": "BG: Dambisa, thank you for coming to TED. DM: Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
